</node>
<node id="Piece-Rate Worker">
  <data key="d0">Piece-Rate Worker</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A piece-rate worker is a laborer whose compensation is determined based on the quantity of work completed, subject to statutory working hour and remuneration standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320345</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 36">
  <data key="d0">Article 36</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 36 specifies the statutory working hour system in Chinese labor law, which serves as the basis for determining labor quotas and remuneration under Article 37.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 36 is a specific provision in Chinese labor law that establishes the standard working hours system.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 36 is a statutory provision governing standard working hours and rest periods, which certain enterprises may be exempted from applying.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-225b307bc1363ee71949e25c8ac697f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8091f80b54e6c94fc8302e0ea487ae6e</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320684</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Law of the People's Republic of China">
  <data key="d0">Labor Law of the People's Republic of China</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Law of the People's Republic of China is the overarching legal framework containing Articles 36 and 37, governing employment conditions, working hours, and remuneration standards.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Law of the People's Republic of China is a legal framework established to protect workers' rights, regulate labor relations, and support socialist market economy development.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Law of the People's Republic of China is the foundational legal framework governing employment relationships, within which Article 94 is situated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Insurance Fund Administration Agency">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance Fund Administration Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Social Insurance Fund Administration Agency is responsible for the collection, management, and operation of social insurance funds in accordance with the law, and bears the responsibility for preserving and increasing the value of these funds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d4778fa05214fc08dae5f90c37126391</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320347</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Insurance Fund Supervisory Agency">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance Fund Supervisory Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Social Insurance Fund Supervisory Agency is responsible for supervising the collection, management, and operation of social insurance funds in accordance with the law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d4778fa05214fc08dae5f90c37126391</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320347</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Insurance Fund">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance Fund</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Social Insurance Fund is a legally mandated fund used to provide social insurance benefits, subject to strict rules on collection, management, operation, supervision, and protection against misuse.&lt;SEP&gt;The Social Insurance Fund is a financial mechanism established by the State to support the provision of social insurance benefits.&lt;SEP&gt;The Social Insurance Fund is a financial resource established to provide social security benefits, including pensions, medical care, unemployment, work injury, and maternity insurance.&lt;SEP&gt;The Social Insurance Fund is a financial mechanism whose funding sources are determined by insurance type and which is gradually implementing social pooling.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d4778fa05214fc08dae5f90c37126391&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7f12b62d488f4ca39157007ee023697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6caf56110d85965c35a028c39252a52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320812</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Seventy-Four">
  <data key="d0">Article Seventy-Four</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Seventy-Four is a legal provision stipulating the responsibilities of social insurance fund administration and supervisory agencies, and prohibiting the misappropriation of social insurance funds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d4778fa05214fc08dae5f90c37126391</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320347</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Any Organization or Individual">
  <data key="d0">Any Organization or Individual</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d4778fa05214fc08dae5f90c37126391</data>
  <data key="d2">The law explicitly prohibits any organization or individual from misappropriating the Social Insurance Fund, ensuring its dedicated use and legal protection.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320349</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Special Operations Workers">
  <data key="d0">Special Operations Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Special operations workers are laborers who must undergo specialized training and obtain certification to perform hazardous or specialized tasks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-532fb6a3f85ff55e73d76c3c0830e0c0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320361</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Specialized Training">
  <data key="d0">Specialized Training</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Specialized training is a mandatory educational process required for special operations workers to acquire necessary skills and safety knowledge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-532fb6a3f85ff55e73d76c3c0830e0c0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320361</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Special Operations Qualification">
  <data key="d0">Special Operations Qualification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Special operations qualification is a formal certification granted upon successful completion of specialized training, authorizing individuals to perform designated special operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-532fb6a3f85ff55e73d76c3c0830e0c0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320361</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 55">
  <data key="d0">Article 55</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 55 is a regulatory provision stipulating that workers engaged in special operations must undergo specialized training and obtain corresponding qualifications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-532fb6a3f85ff55e73d76c3c0830e0c0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320361</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Laborer">
  <data key="d0">Laborer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Laborer is an individual who enters into a labor contract with an employer and is governed by labor law in multiple interrelated dimensions. As a party to such a contract, the Laborer is subject to statutory provisions concerning contract termination—including obligations to provide written notice when initiating termination—and is bound by ancillary legal duties such as confidentiality. The Laborer performs work under this contractual relationship and is entitled to receive wages, including payment during statutory holidays, marriage leave, bereavement leave, and lawful participation in social activities. Beyond remuneration, the Laborer is guaranteed access to social insurance benefits under legally defined circumstances, reflecting the protective framework of labor legislation.

The Laborer also holds substantive rights aimed at safeguarding dignity, equity, and voice in the workplace. These include protection from discrimination under Article 12 of applicable labor law and the right to participate democratically in enterprise management or engage in equal negotiations with employers concerning the protection of lawful rights and interests. Collectively, these rights and obligations position the Laborer not merely as a service provider but as a legally recognized subject with enforceable entitlements and procedural safeguards embedded in national labor regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;The laborer is an individual who has the right to terminate the labor contract under specific circumstances outlined in Article 32.&lt;SEP&gt;A laborer is a worker who has the legal right to join and form trade unions.&lt;SEP&gt;A laborer is an individual who works for an employer and is protected under labor law from unjust termination in specific circumstances.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f58679d44bde34664e3b2b1d8d81021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1005fcbd1306706f050d1a4d82ca943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7772034814a251985224602f1dd80c02&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Contract is a legally binding agreement that formally establishes and governs the employment relationship between an employer and an employee—or, equivalently, a worker and an employer. As a foundational legal instrument, it defines the mutual rights, obligations, and responsibilities of both parties throughout the duration of employment and is explicitly regulated by national or regional labor law. The contract must be entered into voluntarily and, in many jurisdictions, is required to be in written form and include specific mandatory clauses—such as compensation, working hours, job duties, workplace safety provisions, and conditions for termination—to ensure enforceability and statutory worker protection.

Core structural elements commonly stipulated in a Labor Contract include provisions for a probationary period, during which either party may assess suitability under mutually agreed terms; detailed grounds, procedures, and potential severance entitlements associated with termination; and mechanisms for resolving disputes in alignment with labor standards and regulatory frameworks. Its legal significance extends beyond defining work expectations: it serves as a primary tool for enforcing statutory protections, upholding labor rights, and adjudicating liabilities—including those arising under specific legal provisions, such as Article 99, where termination status directly determines employer liability. Across all descriptions, the Labor Contract is consistently characterized as a formal, legally enforceable instrument subject to compliance with applicable labor legislation and integral to maintaining equitable and lawful employment relations.&lt;SEP&gt;The labor contract is a legally binding agreement between the laborer and employer, defining rights, obligations, and conditions of employment.&lt;SEP&gt;A labor contract is a legal agreement between an employer and employee, governed by principles of equality, voluntariness, and mutual consultation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8312a3dee9750ae6ed96f0944844f476&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d41ba7cc39eba05754bf473088deb752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a27b67d73b4ed3925ff3ffe1e99ca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7440e9a9d68a40eb06fc88eaf48bf3a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2c130666c9b8351b89ec909dc97396f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16710c0d4227925f557982746f69c1b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1e934469e0af82604f570bd7744c5cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1affc2633f7ab17127fc986e6c20944&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1a4ebf44debb9e60481cc178f07fa11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c60e5be371dfa1f9ec2c3f41c6c51bea</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Probation Period">
  <data key="d0">Probation Period</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The probation period is a trial phase in a labor contract during which the employer may assess whether the laborer meets the employment requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The probation period is a trial phase at the beginning of employment during which either party may terminate the labor contract more freely.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Discipline">
  <data key="d0">Labor Discipline</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor discipline refers to the behavioral standards and rules established by the employer that laborers are required to follow.&lt;SEP&gt;Labor discipline is a mandatory clause outlining expected conduct, rules, and behavioral standards in the workplace.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2c130666c9b8351b89ec909dc97396f</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320650</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employer's Rules and Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Employer's Rules and Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Employer's rules and regulations are formal internal policies that govern employee conduct and operational procedures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Negligence">
  <data key="d0">Gross Negligence</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross negligence is a serious failure in performing duties, resulting in significant harm to the employer's interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Embezzlement and Fraud">
  <data key="d0">Embezzlement and Fraud</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Embezzlement and fraud refer to intentional unlawful acts by a laborer for personal gain that damage the employer's interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Criminal Liability">
  <data key="d0">Criminal Liability</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Criminal liability arises when a laborer is formally prosecuted and held legally accountable for committing a crime.&lt;SEP&gt;Criminal Liability is the legal consequence imposed on responsible personnel when their actions constitute a crime under Article 96.&lt;SEP&gt;Criminal Liability refers to the legal responsibility imposed on individuals who commit crimes, including penalties such as imprisonment or fines.&lt;SEP&gt;Criminal Liability refers to legal responsibility imposed when staff members commit crimes such as abuse of power, dereliction of duty, or favoritism.&lt;SEP&gt;Criminal liability refers to legal responsibility under the Criminal Law for serious negligence leading to major accidents.&lt;SEP&gt;Criminal Liability refers to the legal responsibility for criminal acts, which may be imposed on responsible personnel if obstruction or retaliation constitutes a crime under Article 101.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7f12b62d488f4ca39157007ee023697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321276</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Twenty-Five">
  <data key="d0">Article Twenty-Five</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Twenty-Five is a provision in Chinese labor law specifying circumstances under which an employer may lawfully terminate a labor contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320369</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Termination">
  <data key="d0">Contract Termination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract termination refers to the cessation of a labor contract upon fulfillment of statutory or agreed conditions, such as expiration of term or occurrence of stipulated termination events.&lt;SEP&gt;Contract termination is the legal process by which a labor contract is ended, permitted here upon mutual agreement of the parties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8312a3dee9750ae6ed96f0944844f476&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16710c0d4227925f557982746f69c1b2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320713</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 23">
  <data key="d0">Article 23</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 23 is a provision in Chinese labor law specifying the conditions under which a labor contract terminates automatically.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8312a3dee9750ae6ed96f0944844f476</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320373</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chinese Labor Law">
  <data key="d0">Chinese Labor Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chinese Labor Law is the statutory legal framework governing employment relationships in China, within which Article 23 is situated.&lt;SEP&gt;Chinese Labor Law is the legal framework governing labor relations and establishing special protections for female workers and minor workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8312a3dee9750ae6ed96f0944844f476&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320494</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Collective Contract">
  <data key="d0">Collective Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A collective contract is a legally binding agreement signed in accordance with the law that applies to both the enterprise and all its employees.&lt;SEP&gt;A Collective Contract is a legally binding agreement covering labor remuneration, working hours, rest and vacation, occupational safety and health, insurance, and welfare.&lt;SEP&gt;A collective contract is an agreement negotiated between employers and a labor union representing employees, covering working conditions and rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Collective contract is an agreement negotiated between employers and worker representatives (e.g., unions) covering terms and conditions for a group of workers, as referenced in the chapter title.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96ddd1389a8d1afebfed70b7a0051cd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d41ba7cc39eba05754bf473088deb752&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320933</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Enterprise">
  <data key="d0">Enterprise</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">An enterprise is a business entity bound by the collective contract and responsible for complying with its provisions regarding labor conditions and remuneration.&lt;SEP&gt;The Enterprise is the employer entity that engages in collective contract negotiations with its employees.&lt;SEP&gt;An enterprise is a business entity that may apply for alternative work and rest arrangements due to its production characteristics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96ddd1389a8d1afebfed70b7a0051cd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8091f80b54e6c94fc8302e0ea487ae6e</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320684</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employee">
  <data key="d0">Employee</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Employee is a worker who enters into a labor contract with an employer, forming the individual party to that agreement and assuming obligations to perform work duties as specified in the contract. As such, the Employee is bound by contractual terms including confidentiality obligations concerning the employer’s commercial secrets. The Employee’s rights and protections are grounded in both individual labor contracts and broader regulatory frameworks, particularly where collective contracts apply: in such cases, the individual labor contract must meet or exceed the standards established collectively. The Employee is entitled to economic compensation under specified legal conditions, including termination of the contract—whether lawfully initiated by the employer (e.g., due to inability to perform work after medical leave or failure to meet job requirements) or unlawfully executed (e.g., through unjustified dismissal or delayed contract signing). Additionally, the Employee is legally guaranteed labor safety and hygiene conditions, access to appropriate protective equipment, and mandatory regular health checks—especially when engaged in hazardous occupations. Should the employment contract be deemed invalid, the Employee is recognized as the party suffering damage and is therefore entitled to compensation. Thus, the Employee occupies a dual role: as a duty-bound contractual party obligated to fulfill agreed-upon responsibilities, and as a legally protected individual vested with enforceable rights across dimensions of remuneration, health and safety, procedural fairness, and redress for contractual violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96ddd1389a8d1afebfed70b7a0051cd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e04f20b8b7b250ab2854ffab0ad26c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73b6c9297c7a7da453da3a92e368350a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1affc2633f7ab17127fc986e6c20944&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1a4ebf44debb9e60481cc178f07fa11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Individual Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Individual Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">An individual labor contract is an agreement between an employee and an enterprise specifying labor conditions and remuneration, required to meet minimum standards established by the collective contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96ddd1389a8d1afebfed70b7a0051cd8</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320387</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 35">
  <data key="d0">Article 35</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 35 is a legal provision stipulating that legally signed collective contracts bind both the enterprise and all its employees, and that individual labor contracts must meet or exceed the labor conditions and remuneration standards set in the collective contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96ddd1389a8d1afebfed70b7a0051cd8</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320387</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Worker">
  <data key="d0">Worker</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Worker is an individual who enters into a labor relationship with an employer through a formal labor contract, thereby establishing legally recognized employment status. As such, the Worker is entitled to core statutory protections and benefits under labor law, including receipt of wages no lower than the locally prescribed minimum wage standard, eligibility for overtime pay in accordance with regulatory stipulations, and guaranteed access to statutory holidays. The Worker is also required to participate in the national social insurance system, entailing both entitlement to coverage and the obligation to pay applicable social insurance premiums.

In carrying out assigned duties, the Worker must strictly abide by safety operating procedures during the work process, reflecting a shared responsibility for occupational health and safety. While the Worker operates under the employer’s direction—including adherence to work orders—the legal framework imposes health safeguards when working hours are extended under specific conditions, acknowledging potential risks associated with prolonged labor. Notably, one description indicates the Worker may be subject to potentially unsafe work orders; this introduces tension with the requirement to follow safety procedures and suggests an area of regulatory vulnerability or contested interpretation—where legal protections may exist in principle but face practical enforcement challenges. Collectively, these descriptions portray the Worker as a rights-bearing yet structurally subordinate party within a regulated labor relationship, defined by contractual formality, statutory entitlements, procedural obligations, and embedded power asymmetries.&lt;SEP&gt;A worker is an individual employed under a labor contract and whose actions may trigger legal liabilities for employers.&lt;SEP&gt;A worker is an individual employed by an employer and protected under labor law provisions on working time.&lt;SEP&gt;The Worker is a party in labor disputes and is entitled to rest, recuperation, convalescence, and protection of lawful rights and interests during dispute resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;The worker is the individual employed by the employer and entitled to at least one day of rest per week.&lt;SEP&gt;A person engaged in labor who is protected under the reporting and handling system for workplace accidents and occupational diseases.&lt;SEP&gt;The worker is an individual employed by an employer and entitled to labor safety protections, whose life and property may be harmed due to safety failures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-900f9424a8f6a615634cfe7eb308739e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7440e9a9d68a40eb06fc88eaf48bf3a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ade40507636905dbb256fde347d4c4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6caf56110d85965c35a028c39252a52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd1fd3462e1832af7cfde4c6f880f76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1b224bc392defbea2ebc9ea123f70db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Overtime Work">
  <data key="d0">Overtime Work</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Overtime Work refers to work performed beyond normal working hours, triggering higher wage compensation requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Overtime work is prohibited for pregnant women beyond seven months and for women during lactation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rest Day Work">
  <data key="d0">Rest Day Work</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rest Day Work refers to work scheduled on designated rest days without compensatory time off, requiring double wage payment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320391</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Statutory Holiday Work">
  <data key="d0">Statutory Holiday Work</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Statutory Holiday Work refers to work performed on officially recognized public holidays, requiring triple wage payment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320391</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 44">
  <data key="d0">Article 44</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 44 is a provision in China's Labor Law specifying mandatory overtime wage standards for employers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320391</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="China's Labor Law">
  <data key="d0">China's Labor Law</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">China's Labor Law is the overarching legal framework containing Article 44 and governing labor relations, working hours, and wage standards in China.&lt;SEP&gt;China's Labor Law is the statutory legal framework governing labor relations, including working hours, rest periods, and protections for workers.&lt;SEP&gt;China's Labor Law is the statutory framework containing Article 99, which governs employer liability in cases of hiring workers still under existing labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320889</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Enterprise Employee Party">
  <data key="d0">Enterprise Employee Party</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Enterprise Employee Party refers to the collective body of employees in an enterprise who negotiate labor-related matters with the enterprise.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employee Representative Congress">
  <data key="d0">Employee Representative Congress</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Employee Representative Congress is a deliberative body through which draft collective contracts are discussed and approved.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Trade Union">
  <data key="d0">Trade Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Trade Union represents employees in signing collective contracts with enterprises where it is established.&lt;SEP&gt;The Trade Union participates in labor dispute mediation through representation on the Labor Dispute Mediation Committee and appoints its chairperson.&lt;SEP&gt;The trade union is a representative body that must be consulted by the employer prior to staff reductions, as stipulated in the regulation.&lt;SEP&gt;A trade union represents and safeguards the legitimate rights and interests of laborers and conducts activities independently in accordance with the law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7772034814a251985224602f1dd80c02</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321227</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employee-Designated Representative">
  <data key="d0">Employee-Designated Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">An Employee-Designated Representative is a person elected by employees to sign collective contracts on their behalf in enterprises without a trade union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Remuneration">
  <data key="d0">Labor Remuneration</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Remuneration refers to the wages and salaries paid to employees, one of the key subjects covered in collective contracts.&lt;SEP&gt;Labor remuneration is a mandatory clause specifying the wages, salary structure, and payment terms for the employee.&lt;SEP&gt;Labor remuneration denotes the wages or compensation owed to the laborer as stipulated in the labor contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2c130666c9b8351b89ec909dc97396f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Working Hours">
  <data key="d0">Working Hours</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Working Hours denotes the scheduled time during which employees are required to work, regulated under collective contracts.&lt;SEP&gt;Working Hours refers to the legally defined or contractually agreed period during which employees are required to perform work.&lt;SEP&gt;Working hours refer to the time during which a worker is required to perform duties for an employer, regulated by the Labor Law.&lt;SEP&gt;Working hours refer to the legally defined duration of employment, and unlawful extension triggers administrative penalties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58cdd101c942cf6d953d675aa6fecbb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd1fd3462e1832af7cfde4c6f880f76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320999</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rest And Vacation">
  <data key="d0">Rest And Vacation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rest And Vacation encompasses statutory rest periods and paid leave entitlements for employees, as stipulated in collective contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Occupational Safety And Health">
  <data key="d0">Occupational Safety And Health</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Occupational Safety And Health covers measures and standards to ensure safe and healthy working conditions, addressed in collective contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insurance And Welfare">
  <data key="d0">Insurance And Welfare</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Insurance And Welfare includes social insurance contributions and supplementary welfare benefits negotiated between employees and enterprises.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-31e42e6a06e7bc74c1fb5360756f9132</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320413</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State">
  <data key="d0">State</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The State refers to the national government of China, which serves as the central authority responsible for comprehensive labor governance, social welfare development, and economic policy implementation. It enacts and enforces labor protection laws—particularly those safeguarding female and minor workers—and establishes binding labor standards across sectors. In the domain of employment, the State actively promotes job creation by fostering economic and social development, supporting individual business operations, and expanding employment opportunities through targeted initiatives. To enhance workforce capability and adaptability, it develops vocational training programs and vocational education systems, while also determining occupational classifications to standardize labor market structures.

The State plays a pivotal role in social security architecture, establishing and improving social insurance systems—including pension, medical, unemployment, work-related injury, and maternity insurance—for both employers and workers. It encourages and promotes insurance-related policies to broaden coverage and strengthen risk protection. Complementing this, the State develops social welfare undertakings and constructs public welfare facilities—such as rest homes, sanatoriums, and convalescent centers—to support workers’ rest, recuperation, and overall well-being. Furthermore, it regulates income distribution to advance fairness and coordinates labor relations to maintain industrial harmony. Collectively, these functions reflect the State’s integrated mandate to ensure labor rights, foster inclusive growth, and sustain long-term socioeconomic stability in China.&lt;SEP&gt;The State refers to the national government of China, which establishes systems for reporting and handling workplace accidents and occupational diseases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4854ca3e86ea91f91e6984abe5fcda52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321061</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vocational Training">
  <data key="d0">Vocational Training</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vocational training is a state-supported initiative aimed at developing workers' occupational skills, improving worker quality, and enhancing employment and job capabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Vocational Training refers to education and instruction focused on developing specific skills for employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12cdd7ef2f5ab7ae8af0f7aa527a5494</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Insurance">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social insurance is a state-developed system that provides assistance and compensation to workers in cases of old age, illness, work-related injury, unemployment, and childbirth.&lt;SEP&gt;Social insurance is a public welfare system improved by the State to provide financial protection to workers in cases such as unemployment, illness, or retirement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Occupational Classification">
  <data key="d0">Occupational Classification</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Occupational classification is a system determined by the State to categorize professions and underpin the development of occupational skill standards and certification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vocational Skill Standards">
  <data key="d0">Vocational Skill Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vocational skill standards are official benchmarks established by the State for specified occupations to guide training and assessment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Professional Qualification Certificate System">
  <data key="d0">Professional Qualification Certificate System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The professional qualification certificate system is a State-mandated framework requiring certification for certain occupations, administered by registered assessment institutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="People's Governments at All Levels">
  <data key="d0">People's Governments at All Levels</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">People's Governments at All Levels are local administrative bodies required to integrate vocational training development into socioeconomic planning and encourage diverse stakeholders to conduct such training.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employers">
  <data key="d0">Employers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Employers are obligated to establish vocational training systems, allocate and use vocational training funds as prescribed, and conduct planned training for workers, especially those in technical trades who must be trained before上岗(taking up their posts).&lt;SEP&gt;Employers are entities obligated to comply with labor protection regulations, including assigning appropriate work and conducting health checks for minor workers.&lt;SEP&gt;Employers are entities responsible for labor management and are encouraged by the State to establish supplementary insurance for their workers.&lt;SEP&gt;Employers include enterprises and individual economic organizations within the People's Republic of China, as well as state organs, public institutions, and social organizations that establish labor contract relationships with workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Workers">
  <data key="d0">Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Workers are individuals whose occupational skills, quality, employment capacity, and work capacity are enhanced through vocational training, and who are entitled to social insurance benefits under specified life circumstances.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are individuals employed under labor contracts and are entitled to paid annual leave after meeting the continuous employment requirement.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are individuals subject to the Labor Hour System, whose daily and weekly working hours are regulated.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are the individuals who participate in social voluntary labor, labor competitions, rationalization proposals, scientific research, technological innovation, and invention activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are individuals employed by employers and are the beneficiaries of supplementary insurance and encouraged to engage in savings-based insurance.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are individuals who voluntarily organize for employment or engage in individual business activities to achieve employment.&lt;SEP&gt;Workers are individuals who form labor relationships with employers and possess rights including equal employment, remuneration, rest and vacation, occupational safety and health protection, vocational training, social insurance, and labor dispute resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8b98b69c20324f8a16d939573b5b8f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-225b307bc1363ee71949e25c8ac697f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4854ca3e86ea91f91e6984abe5fcda52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Assessment and Appraisal Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Assessment and Appraisal Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Assessment and appraisal institutions are entities registered with the State to administer vocational skill assessments and certifications for workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Workers">
  <data key="d0">Technical Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical workers are a category of workers who, by law, must undergo vocational training before commencing work in their designated technical trades.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-302371bc27545b04a86a89dc8b5a11c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320421</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wage Payment">
  <data key="d0">Wage Payment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Wage Payment refers to the legal requirement that wages must be paid in monetary form to workers on a monthly basis.&lt;SEP&gt;Wage payment encompasses timely and full remuneration to workers; withholding or unjustified delay constitutes a violation subject to enforcement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f58679d44bde34664e3b2b1d8d81021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320999</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Law Article 50">
  <data key="d0">Labor Law Article 50</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Law Article 50 stipulates the rules for wage payment, prohibiting unauthorized deductions or unjustified delays.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f58679d44bde34664e3b2b1d8d81021</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320428</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 50">
  <data key="d0">Article 50</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 50 is a provision in China's Labor Law that mandates monthly monetary wage payment to workers and prohibits unauthorized deductions or unjustified delays.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f58679d44bde34664e3b2b1d8d81021</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320428</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Safety and Health Facilities">
  <data key="d0">Labor Safety and Health Facilities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor safety and health facilities refer to infrastructure and equipment designed to ensure worker safety and health, mandated to meet national standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Standards">
  <data key="d0">National Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">National standards are official benchmarks established by the state for labor safety and health facilities, requiring compliance in all relevant engineering projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="New Construction Projects">
  <data key="d0">New Construction Projects</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">New construction projects are engineering endeavors that must integrate labor safety and health facilities simultaneously with the main project in design, construction, and commissioning.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Renovation Projects">
  <data key="d0">Renovation Projects</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Renovation projects are engineering endeavors that must integrate labor safety and health facilities simultaneously with the main project in design, construction, and commissioning.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Expansion Projects">
  <data key="d0">Expansion Projects</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Expansion projects are engineering endeavors that must integrate labor safety and health facilities simultaneously with the main project in design, construction, and commissioning.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Simultaneous Design">
  <data key="d0">Simultaneous Design</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Simultaneous design is a regulatory requirement mandating that labor safety and health facilities be planned concurrently with the main engineering project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Simultaneous Construction">
  <data key="d0">Simultaneous Construction</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Simultaneous construction is a regulatory requirement mandating that labor safety and health facilities be built concurrently with the main engineering project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Simultaneous Commissioning">
  <data key="d0">Simultaneous Commissioning</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Simultaneous commissioning is a regulatory requirement mandating that labor safety and health facilities be put into production and use concurrently with the main engineering project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320449</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 53">
  <data key="d0">Article 53</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 53 is a legal provision stipulating requirements for labor safety and health facilities in engineering projects.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ff0cf62a6db3fe1d75880bb84131de82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320450</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Minimum Wage Guarantee System">
  <data key="d0">Minimum Wage Guarantee System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Minimum Wage Guarantee System is a national policy ensuring that workers receive wages not below a government-mandated minimum level.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320453</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Provincial People's Government">
  <data key="d0">Provincial People's Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Provincial People's Government is responsible for setting the specific minimum wage standards within its administrative region.&lt;SEP&gt;The Provincial People's Government is the administrative authority of a province, autonomous region, or municipality directly under the Central Government, responsible for implementing labor contract regulations in accordance with national law and local conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Autonomous Region People's Government">
  <data key="d0">Autonomous Region People's Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Autonomous Region People's Government is responsible for setting the specific minimum wage standards within its administrative region.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320453</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Municipality People's Government">
  <data key="d0">Municipality People's Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Municipality People's Government is responsible for setting the specific minimum wage standards within its administrative region.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320453</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Council">
  <data key="d0">State Council</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The State Council is the highest executive organ of state power in China and receives备案(filing) of minimum wage standards from local governments.&lt;SEP&gt;The State Council is the highest executive organ of state power in China, responsible for formulating the specific implementation measures for the national paid annual leave system.&lt;SEP&gt;The State Council is the highest executive organ of state power in the People's Republic of China and receives备案(filing) of local implementation plans for labor contract systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8b98b69c20324f8a16d939573b5b8f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Minimum Wage Standard">
  <data key="d0">Minimum Wage Standard</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Minimum Wage Standard is a legally defined threshold for wages, set by provincial-level governments and filed with the State Council, which employers must observe.&lt;SEP&gt;The Minimum Wage Standard is a regulatory benchmark for the lowest remuneration employers may legally pay workers, determined and adjusted based on multiple socioeconomic factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add1965d088b328f8a7f228f9ba5c825</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320951</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 48">
  <data key="d0">Article 48</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 48 is a provision in Chinese labor law that establishes the Minimum Wage Guarantee System and defines related responsibilities and obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320454</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Public Security Organs">
  <data key="d0">Public Security Organs</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Public Security Organs are the law enforcement authorities empowered to impose administrative penalties such as detention, fines, or warnings on responsible personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Responsible Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Responsible Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Responsible Personnel are individuals held accountable for unlawful employer conduct and subject to administrative or criminal penalties.&lt;SEP&gt;Responsible Personnel are individuals held legally accountable, including potential criminal liability, for failing to address accident hazards that result in major accidents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 96">
  <data key="d0">Article 96</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 96 is a legal provision specifying penalties for employers who use coercive means to force labor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Forced Labor">
  <data key="d0">Forced Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Forced Labor refers to labor imposed through violence, threats, or illegal restriction of personal freedom, prohibited under Article 96.&lt;SEP&gt;Forced labor refers to work compelled by violence, threats, or unlawful restriction of personal freedom, which entitles the laborer to immediate termination of the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Violence">
  <data key="d0">Violence</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Violence is one of the coercive means prohibited under Article 96 for forcing labor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Threat">
  <data key="d0">Threat</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Threat is a prohibited method used to compel labor, as specified in Article 96.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Illegal Restriction of Personal Freedom">
  <data key="d0">Illegal Restriction of Personal Freedom</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Illegal Restriction of Personal Freedom is a prohibited coercive measure for forcing labor under Article 96.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc2cc869b28e0784bd829a72850245ab</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320473</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter Four">
  <data key="d0">Chapter Four</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter Four is titled "Working Hours and Rest and Vacation" and is part of a larger document or regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-58cdd101c942cf6d953d675aa6fecbb1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rest and Vacation">
  <data key="d0">Rest and Vacation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Rest and Vacation encompasses statutory rest periods, holidays, and leave entitlements granted to employees for recuperation and personal time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-58cdd101c942cf6d953d675aa6fecbb1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Female Workers">
  <data key="d0">Female Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Female workers are a protected group under labor law, entitled to special protections during menstruation, pregnancy, and lactation.&lt;SEP&gt;Female workers are a protected group under labor laws, entitled to special protections as outlined in Chapter Seven.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cdfe4fd7432c0c1b10d2636d5f862da7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321260</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Minor Workers">
  <data key="d0">Minor Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Minor workers are defined as laborers aged sixteen to under eighteen years old and are subject to special labor protections.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mine Underground Work">
  <data key="d0">Mine Underground Work</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Mine underground work is prohibited for both female workers and minor workers under Chinese labor law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fourth-Level Physical Labor Intensity">
  <data key="d0">Fourth-Level Physical Labor Intensity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fourth-level physical labor intensity is a classification of strenuous work prohibited for female and minor workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third-Level Physical Labor Intensity">
  <data key="d0">Third-Level Physical Labor Intensity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Third-level physical labor intensity is a classification of strenuous work prohibited for female workers during menstruation, pregnancy, and lactation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Menstruation">
  <data key="d0">Menstruation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Menstruation is a physiological condition during which female workers must be protected from high-altitude, low-temperature, cold-water, and third-level physical labor intensity work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pregnancy">
  <data key="d0">Pregnancy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pregnancy is a protected condition during which female workers must not be assigned third-level physical labor intensity work or prohibited tasks, and those over seven months pregnant must not be assigned overtime or night shifts.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnancy is a protected physiological condition for female laborers, during which termination of employment is prohibited.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lactation">
  <data key="d0">Lactation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Lactation refers to the period when a female worker is nursing an infant under one year old, during which she must not be assigned third-level physical labor intensity work or prohibited tasks, nor overtime or night shifts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ninety-Day Maternity Leave">
  <data key="d0">Ninety-Day Maternity Leave</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ninety-day maternity leave is the minimum statutory leave period granted to female workers upon childbirth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Health Check">
  <data key="d0">Health Check</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Health check is a mandatory periodic medical examination required for minor workers by employers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Night Shift Work">
  <data key="d0">Night Shift Work</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Night shift work is prohibited for pregnant women beyond seven months and for women during lactation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Toxic and Harmful Work">
  <data key="d0">Toxic and Harmful Work</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Toxic and harmful work is prohibited for minor workers under Chinese labor law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c5e2a3fc3ae04a7ea467816a16c1b275</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320493</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Contract Law Article 20">
  <data key="d0">Labor Contract Law Article 20</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 20 of the Labor Contract Law specifies the types of labor contract durations, including fixed-term, open-ended, and task-based contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fixed-Term Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Fixed-Term Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A fixed-term labor contract is a type of employment agreement with a defined start and end date, as stipulated in Article 20 of the Labor Contract Law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Open-Ended Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Open-Ended Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An open-ended labor contract is a type of employment agreement without a predetermined termination date, applicable under conditions such as ten years of continuous service with the same employer, as outlined in Article 20.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Task-Based Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Task-Based Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A task-based labor contract is a type of employment agreement that ends upon completion of a specific work assignment, as defined in Article 20 of the Labor Contract Law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ten-Year Continuous Employment">
  <data key="d0">Ten-Year Continuous Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ten-year continuous employment refers to a condition under which an employee working for the same employer for over ten years may be entitled to an open-ended labor contract, per Article 20.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320499</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Contract Law">
  <data key="d0">Labor Contract Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Contract Law is a legal framework governing employment relationships in China, within which Article 20 is situated.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Contract Law is a statutory framework governing labor contracts, including conditions for termination and confidentiality obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Contract Law is the legal framework governing employment relationships in China, including provisions on contract termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d8dbf846bb0ff55e508ce6be270bcf82&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter Six Labor Safety and Health">
  <data key="d0">Chapter Six Labor Safety and Health</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter Six Labor Safety and Health is a section title addressing regulations and practices related to workplace safety and occupational health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-22d5330489b1dbcbefb33a429cb22bde</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320505</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Written Notice">
  <data key="d0">Written Notice</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Written notice is the formal, documented communication required for a laborer to terminate a labor contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Written Notice is a formal procedural requirement mandating that an Employer provide thirty days’ advance written communication to an Employee prior to contract termination under specified statutory grounds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320879</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Thirty-Day Notice Period">
  <data key="d0">Thirty-Day Notice Period</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The thirty-day notice period is the mandatory timeframe a laborer must observe before terminating a labor contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Thirty-One">
  <data key="d0">Article Thirty-One</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Thirty-One is a provision in Chinese labor law specifying the procedure for laborers to terminate employment contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wage Distribution Method">
  <data key="d0">Wage Distribution Method</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The wage distribution method refers to the system or approach used by an employer to allocate wages among employees, determined autonomously in accordance with legal provisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-35ee711c6a1d7e90851eb7505f271fc1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wage Level">
  <data key="d0">Wage Level</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The wage level denotes the overall standard or scale of remuneration set by an employer, determined based on operational characteristics, economic performance, and legal requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Wage level denotes the general standard or amount of wages, which is to be progressively raised in line with economic development.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-35ee711c6a1d7e90851eb7505f271fc1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320764</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operational Characteristics">
  <data key="d0">Operational Characteristics</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Operational characteristics describe the distinctive features of an employer’s production and business activities that influence wage-related decisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-35ee711c6a1d7e90851eb7505f271fc1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Economic Performance">
  <data key="d0">Economic Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economic performance refers to the financial results and operational efficiency of an employer, serving as a key factor in determining wage distribution and levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-35ee711c6a1d7e90851eb7505f271fc1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 47">
  <data key="d0">Article 47</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 47 is a legal provision stipulating that employers may autonomously determine wage distribution methods and wage levels based on their operational characteristics and economic performance, in accordance with the law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-35ee711c6a1d7e90851eb7505f271fc1</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320519</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Paid Annual Leave System">
  <data key="d0">National Paid Annual Leave System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The National Paid Annual Leave System is a labor policy in China that guarantees paid time off for workers who have been employed continuously for over one year.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a8b98b69c20324f8a16d939573b5b8f0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320526</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 45">
  <data key="d0">Article 45</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 45 is a provision in Chinese labor law that establishes the national paid annual leave system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a8b98b69c20324f8a16d939573b5b8f0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320526</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Economic Compensation">
  <data key="d0">Economic Compensation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economic compensation is a statutory payment required to be provided by the employer to the employee upon termination of the labor contract under certain legal circumstances.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic compensation is a statutory monetary remedy mandated under Article 91 for certain labor rights violations, distinct from wage restitution or damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320999</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 24">
  <data key="d0">Article 24</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 24 is a provision in the Labor Law specifying conditions under which an employer may terminate a labor contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 24 is a provision in Chinese labor law stating that a labor contract may be terminated upon mutual agreement of the contracting parties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16710c0d4227925f557982746f69c1b2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320713</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 26">
  <data key="d0">Article 26</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 26 is a provision in the Labor Law specifying conditions under which an employer may terminate a labor contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 26 is a provision in Chinese labor law specifying conditions under which an employer may lawfully terminate a labor contract with advance written notice.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 26 is a provision in the Labor Contract Law outlining grounds for lawful termination of labor contracts by employers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 27">
  <data key="d0">Article 27</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 27 is a provision in the Labor Law specifying conditions under which an employer may terminate a labor contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 27 is a provision in the Labor Contract Law addressing economic layoff procedures and conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321256</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Law">
  <data key="d0">Labor Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Law is the primary statutory and national legal framework governing labor relations and employment relationships in China. It serves as the overarching legal instrument that regulates key aspects of the employer-employee relationship, including the formation and termination of labor contracts, statutory requirements for economic compensation upon dismissal or contract expiration, and protections for workers’ fundamental rights.  

The Labor Law establishes binding standards for working conditions, notably setting statutory limits on working hours, mandating rest periods and weekly days off, and defining minimum entitlements to paid annual holidays. Specific provisions—such as Articles 36, 38, and 39—address regular working hours, rest intervals, and exceptions applicable to certain enterprises, while Article 42 outlines additional permissible deviations under defined circumstances. Article 105 situates the Labor Law within the broader hierarchy of Chinese labor legislation, underscoring its foundational role.  

Beyond temporal regulations, the Labor Law also governs occupational safety, wage protections, and the formulation and enforcement of internal labor regulations by employers. It codifies procedural and substantive safeguards for employees, ensuring that contractual and non-contractual labor rights are uniformly upheld across sectors. As the core legislative pillar of China’s labor governance system, the Labor Law integrates substantive rights, procedural obligations, and structural exceptions into a coherent, enforceable framework applicable nationwide.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ade40507636905dbb256fde347d4c4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8091f80b54e6c94fc8302e0ea487ae6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dd1fd3462e1832af7cfde4c6f880f76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f106d130307ad6bf0bdf62f720f8c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321176</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 28">
  <data key="d0">Article 28</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 28 is a provision in the Labor Law specifying that employers must provide economic compensation when terminating labor contracts under Articles 24, 26, and 27.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320547</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 42">
  <data key="d0">Article 42</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 42 is a legal provision specifying exceptions to restrictions on extended working hours under certain emergency or statutory conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320556</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 41">
  <data key="d0">Article 41</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 41 is a legal provision that sets general limits on extended working hours, from which Article 42 provides exemptions.&lt;SEP&gt;Article 41 is a provision from China's Labor Law that regulates the conditions and limits for extending working hours, requiring consultation with the labor union and workers and safeguarding worker health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320789</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural Disaster">
  <data key="d0">Natural Disaster</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A natural disaster is an event threatening workers’ life, health, and property safety, triggering exemption from working hour restrictions under Article 42.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320556</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Accident">
  <data key="d0">Accident</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">An accident is an unforeseen event threatening workers’ life, health, and property safety, qualifying for exemption from working hour restrictions under Article 42.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320556</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Equipment Failure">
  <data key="d0">Equipment Failure</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Equipment failure refers to malfunctions of production equipment, transportation lines, or public facilities that affect production or public interests and require immediate repair, justifying extended working hours under Article 42.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5144d09ac2f1a1e98af0cc571325d656</data>
