<node id="Labor Administration Department">
  <data key="d0">Labor Administration Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Administration Department is the government body responsible for reviewing collective labor contracts and raising objections within fifteen days of receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department is the government agency responsible for enforcing labor laws, including ordering employers to pay overdue social insurance fees.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department is a government body responsible for labor-related administrative functions and oversight.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department is the government body responsible for enforcing labor laws and ordering corrections for violations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department is the government body responsible for enforcing labor laws and ordering corrections and imposing fines for violations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department is a government body responsible for supervising labor practices and enforcing labor regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7352b9127a22f0a9251386f17f0f9768&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1c3f29bba2e48ace661e0e106cd6c106&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
