<node id="Workers' Congress">
  <data key="d0">Workers' Congress</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Workers' Congress is a formal mechanism through which laborers participate in democratic management as stipulated by law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Workers' Assembly">
  <data key="d0">Workers' Assembly</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Workers' Assembly is a form of democratic participation used by laborers to manage workplace affairs or negotiate with employers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Rights and Interests of Laborers">
  <data key="d0">Legal Rights and Interests of Laborers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The legal rights and interests of laborers encompass protections guaranteed by law, including those related to employment conditions, safety, compensation, and collective representation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Democratic Management">
  <data key="d0">Democratic Management</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Democratic management refers to the participation of laborers in decision-making processes within their workplace through statutory channels such as workers' congresses or assemblies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Equal Negotiation">
  <data key="d0">Equal Negotiation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Equal negotiation is a legally prescribed method for laborers and employers to discuss and resolve issues concerning labor rights and workplace conditions on a fair and balanced basis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Eight">
  <data key="d0">Article Eight</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Eight is a provision in Chinese labor law that stipulates workers' rights to democratic management and equal negotiation with employers for the protection of their lawful rights and interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320642</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
