<node id="Social Insurance Premium">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance Premium</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social insurance premium refers to mandatory contributions made by employers and employees to national social insurance schemes, including pension, medical, unemployment, work-related injury, and maternity insurance.&lt;SEP&gt;Social insurance premiums are mandatory contributions paid by employers and workers to the Social Insurance Fund.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1c3f29bba2e48ace661e0e106cd6c106&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6caf56110d85965c35a028c39252a52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320812</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Late Payment Surcharge">
  <data key="d0">Late Payment Surcharge</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A late payment surcharge is an additional fee imposed on employers who fail to pay social insurance premiums within the prescribed time limit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1c3f29bba2e48ace661e0e106cd6c106</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
