<node id="Labor Administrative Department">
  <data key="d0">Labor Administrative Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Administrative Department is a government agency operating under the People’s Government at or above the county level, serving as the principal functional authority for labor governance in China. It is legally mandated to supervise and inspect employers’ compliance with labor laws, regulations, and standards—including those governing working hours, rest periods, workplace safety, and occupational health. Among its core enforcement powers, the Labor Administrative Department may issue warnings, order corrective actions, impose administrative fines, and mandate compensation for violations of labor legislation.

In addition to its regulatory and punitive functions, the Labor Administrative Department plays an active role in labor dispute resolution: it is formally represented on the Labor Dispute Arbitration Committee, contributing to oversight and procedural integrity in arbitration proceedings. It also holds statutory authority to approve alternative work and rest arrangements for enterprises—such as flexible scheduling or shift systems—provided these arrangements meet legal requirements and safeguard workers’ rights.

Collectively, the Labor Administrative Department functions as both a preventive supervisor and a responsive enforcer, integrating inspection, education, approval, arbitration participation, and penalty imposition into a comprehensive framework for labor law implementation and worker protection.&lt;SEP&gt;The labor administrative department is the government authority to which employers must report before implementing staff reductions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8091f80b54e6c94fc8302e0ea487ae6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6446a7689e729164af31e8ab0faafc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee12e2672dfb9fc10f84edd44b67880&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
