<node id="Major Casualty Accident">
  <data key="d0">Major Casualty Accident</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A Major Casualty Accident is a serious workplace incident involving significant injury or loss of life resulting from违章冒险作业(violation-risk作业).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Serious Consequences">
  <data key="d0">Serious Consequences</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Serious Consequences refer to the severe outcomes, such as loss of life or critical injury, arising from a major casualty accident.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Criminal Responsibility">
  <data key="d0">Criminal Responsibility</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Criminal Responsibility denotes the legal liability that responsible personnel face under criminal law for causing a major casualty accident through unlawful orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Violation-Risk Work">
  <data key="d0">Violation-Risk Work</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Violation-Risk Work refers to labor activities conducted in breach of safety regulations and involving undue danger to workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320704</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Party">
  <data key="d0">Contract Party</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract party refers to either the employer or the employee involved in negotiating and entering into a labor contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16710c0d4227925f557982746f69c1b2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320712</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mutual Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Mutual Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mutual agreement is the condition under which a labor contract may be terminated, requiring consent from both parties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16710c0d4227925f557982746f69c1b2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320713</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Safety and Hygiene Conditions">
  <data key="d0">Labor Safety and Hygiene Conditions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Safety and Hygiene Conditions refer to workplace standards mandated by national regulations to ensure employee well-being.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e04f20b8b7b250ab2854ffab0ad26c2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320720</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Protective Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Labor Protective Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Protective Equipment consists of necessary gear provided by employers to safeguard employees from occupational hazards.&lt;SEP&gt;Labor protective equipment includes items provided to workers to safeguard against occupational hazards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e04f20b8b7b250ab2854ffab0ad26c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Occupational Health Examination">
  <data key="d0">Occupational Health Examination</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Occupational Health Examination is a periodic medical assessment required for employees engaged in jobs with occupational hazards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e04f20b8b7b250ab2854ffab0ad26c2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320721</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Regulations">
  <data key="d0">National Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">National Regulations refer to the legally binding standards and requirements established by the state governing labor safety, hygiene, protective equipment, and occupational health examinations.&lt;SEP&gt;National regulations are official rules established by the state governing the employment of minors under sixteen in specific sectors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e04f20b8b7b250ab2854ffab0ad26c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Union">
  <data key="d0">Labor Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Union is an organization that represents employees' interests and has the right to review and provide opinions on employer decisions regarding contract termination.&lt;SEP&gt;The labor union is a representative body that collaborates with the employer and workers regarding working hour extensions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f1e934469e0af82604f570bd7744c5cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320788</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law and Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Law and Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Law and Regulations refer to statutory and administrative rules that govern labor relations and must be adhered to by employers in managing labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f1e934469e0af82604f570bd7744c5cb</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320729</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 30">
  <data key="d0">Article 30</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 30 is a provision in Chinese labor law that grants labor unions the right to express opinions when employers unilaterally terminate labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f1e934469e0af82604f570bd7744c5cb</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320729</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Disabled Persons">
  <data key="d0">Disabled Persons</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Disabled persons are individuals with physical or mental impairments who are entitled to special employment provisions under law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ethnic Minority Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Ethnic Minority Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Ethnic minority personnel are members of officially recognized ethnic minority groups in China, granted specific employment protections by law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Demobilized Military Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Demobilized Military Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Demobilized military personnel are individuals who have completed active military service and been discharged, receiving preferential employment treatment under legal provisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment">
  <data key="d0">Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment refers to the engagement in lawful work or occupation, subject to special legal provisions for certain protected groups.&lt;SEP&gt;Employment refers to job opportunities created through economic and social development and expanded business activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Employment is a socio-economic concept representing the state of workers being engaged in labor or self-employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320933</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law And Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Law And Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Law and regulations are formal rules established by state authorities that govern employment practices and provide special provisions for designated groups.&lt;SEP&gt;Law and regulations define the conditions and standards under which laborers enjoy social insurance benefits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1005fcbd1306706f050d1a4d82ca943</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Fourteen">
  <data key="d0">Article Fourteen</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Fourteen is a legal provision specifying employment rules for disabled persons, ethnic minority personnel, and demobilized military personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c42492e507d3ed5394992be8206bb0c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Supplementary Insurance">
  <data key="d0">Supplementary Insurance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Supplementary Insurance is an additional insurance scheme that employers may establish for workers beyond statutory requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Savings-Based Insurance">
  <data key="d0">Savings-Based Insurance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Savings-Based Insurance is a form of personal insurance promoted by the State, emphasizing individual financial planning and security.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 75">
  <data key="d0">Article 75</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 75 is a provision in Chinese law that outlines state encouragement for employers to establish supplementary insurance and promotion of savings-based insurance for workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1833eb6307e64f230db692d0cf7279ca</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 46">
  <data key="d0">Article 46</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 46 is a provision stipulating principles for wage distribution, including distribution according to labor and equal pay for equal work, as well as state macro-control over total wages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320763</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Wage Distribution">
  <data key="d0">Wage Distribution</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Wage distribution refers to the system and principles governing how wages are allocated among workers, emphasizing distribution according to labor and equal pay for equal work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320763</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Equal Pay For Equal Work">
  <data key="d0">Equal Pay For Equal Work</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Equal pay for equal work is a principle requiring that workers performing the same job with the same responsibilities and qualifications receive identical remuneration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320764</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Macro-Control Over Total Wages">
  <data key="d0">State Macro-Control Over Total Wages</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">State macro-control over total wages refers to national-level regulatory measures aimed at managing and guiding the overall scale of wage expenditures in the economy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320764</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distribution According To Labor">
  <data key="d0">Distribution According To Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Distribution according to labor is a principle stating that wages should be allocated based on the quantity and quality of work performed by individuals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ccd272c055ffadcfc0230544b262015</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320764</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Marriage Leave">
  <data key="d0">Marriage Leave</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Marriage leave is a legally stipulated period of absence granted for marriage, during which wage payment by the employer is required.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320768</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bereavement Leave">
  <data key="d0">Bereavement Leave</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Bereavement leave is a legally stipulated period of absence granted for mourning, during which wage payment by the employer is required.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320768</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Activity">
  <data key="d0">Social Activity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social activity refers to lawful civic or public engagements in which laborers may participate, entitling them to wage payment during absence from work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320768</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 51">
  <data key="d0">Article 51</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 51 is a provision in Chinese labor law stipulating that employers must pay wages to laborers during statutory holidays, marriage or bereavement leave, and lawful participation in social activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320768</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter 6">
  <data key="d0">Chapter 6</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter 6 is a section of Chinese labor law titled "Labor Safety and Health", establishing regulatory requirements for occupational safety and hygiene.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320769</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Local People's Governments">
  <data key="d0">Local People's Governments</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Local People's Governments are governmental bodies at various administrative levels in China responsible for implementing policies including employment service development.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7b6eb7df22cbf1e6b2dcf127e89cc5b3</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320778</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vocational Introduction Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Vocational Introduction Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Vocational Introduction Institutions are entities that provide employment services, and the government is mandated to develop multiple types of them.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7b6eb7df22cbf1e6b2dcf127e89cc5b3</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320778</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Services">
  <data key="d0">Employment Services</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment Services refer to support activities aimed at facilitating job matching and labor market participation, as stipulated in the regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7b6eb7df22cbf1e6b2dcf127e89cc5b3</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320778</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 11">
  <data key="d0">Article 11</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 11 is a provision mandating local governments to develop vocational introduction institutions and provide employment services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7b6eb7df22cbf1e6b2dcf127e89cc5b3</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320778</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Extended Working Hours">
  <data key="d0">Extended Working Hours</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Extended working hours refer to additional work time beyond standard hours, permitted only after consultation and subject to health protections.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320789</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Invalid Employment Contract">
  <data key="d0">Invalid Employment Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An Invalid Employment Contract is a contract rendered void due to reasons attributable to the employer, triggering liability for damages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-73b6c9297c7a7da453da3a92e368350a</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320795</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compensation Liability">
  <data key="d0">Compensation Liability</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compensation Liability refers to the legal obligation of the employer to compensate the employee for damages arising from an invalid employment contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Compensation liability refers to the legal obligation of an employer to provide financial redress to a female worker or underage worker harmed due to violation of protective labor provisions.&lt;SEP&gt;Compensation liability refers to the legal obligation of employers to redress harm caused to workers through monetary remedies such as wage restitution, economic compensation, or damages.&lt;SEP&gt;Compensation liability is the legal obligation imposed on a laborer to reimburse the employer for economic losses caused by breach of contract or confidentiality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-73b6c9297c7a7da453da3a92e368350a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 97">
  <data key="d0">Article 97</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 97 is a legal provision stipulating that employers must bear compensation liability for damages caused to employees by invalid employment contracts attributable to the employer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-73b6c9297c7a7da453da3a92e368350a</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320795</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Personnel">
  <data key="d0">State Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">State Personnel refers to individuals who hold positions in state organs and are responsible for public duties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7f12b62d488f4ca39157007ee023697</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320807</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Insurance Fund Management Institutions Staff">
  <data key="d0">Social Insurance Fund Management Institutions Staff</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Staff of Social Insurance Fund Management Institutions are personnel responsible for the administration and management of social insurance funds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7f12b62d488f4ca39157007ee023697</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320807</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 104">
  <data key="d0">Article 104</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 104 is a legal provision stipulating criminal liability for the misappropriation of social insurance funds by state personnel and staff of social insurance fund management institutions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7f12b62d488f4ca39157007ee023697</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320807</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Pooling">
  <data key="d0">Social Pooling</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social pooling is a method of managing the Social Insurance Fund whereby funds are collectively pooled and managed at a societal level.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f6caf56110d85965c35a028c39252a52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320812</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 72">
  <data key="d0">Article 72</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 72 is a legal provision specifying the funding sources and management principles of the Social Insurance Fund, including mandatory participation by employers and workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f6caf56110d85965c35a028c39252a52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320812</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Council Labor Administration Department">
  <data key="d0">State Council Labor Administration Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The State Council Labor Administration Department is the national authority responsible for overseeing labor work across China.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e890e90dedc2136610b35e3511ee4bff</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Local People's Government Labor Administration Department">
  <data key="d0">Local People's Government Labor Administration Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Local People's Government Labor Administration Department at or above the county level is responsible for managing labor work within its administrative jurisdiction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e890e90dedc2136610b35e3511ee4bff</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Work">
  <data key="d0">Labor Work</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor work refers to the administration, regulation, and oversight of employment, labor relations, and workers' rights in China.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e890e90dedc2136610b35e3511ee4bff</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Administrative Region">
  <data key="d0">Administrative Region</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">An administrative region is a geographically defined area under the jurisdiction of a local people's government, where labor work is managed by the corresponding labor administration department.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e890e90dedc2136610b35e3511ee4bff</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Nine">
  <data key="d0">Article Nine</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Nine is a provision specifying the administrative responsibilities of labor administration departments at national and local levels in China.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e890e90dedc2136610b35e3511ee4bff</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320822</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Female Worker">
  <data key="d0">Female Worker</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A female worker is a worker protected under labor law provisions concerning gender-specific rights and workplace safety.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320836</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Underage Worker">
  <data key="d0">Underage Worker</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">An underage worker is a worker below the legal working age, entitled to special protections under labor law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320836</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 95">
  <data key="d0">Article 95</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 95 is a provision in China's Labor Law specifying penalties for employers violating protections for female and underage workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320836</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Safety and Health System">
  <data key="d0">Labor Safety and Health System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Safety and Health System is a mandatory institutional framework that employers must establish and maintain to ensure worker safety and health during employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="National Labor Safety and Health Regulations and Standards">
  <data key="d0">National Labor Safety and Health Regulations and Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">These are official state-mandated rules and benchmarks governing occupational safety and health practices that employers must strictly follow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Safety and Health Education">
  <data key="d0">Labor Safety and Health Education</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Safety and Health Education is a required activity conducted by employers to inform and train workers on safety and health practices in the workplace.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Workplace Accident">
  <data key="d0">Workplace Accident</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A Workplace Accident is an incident occurring during labor processes that employers must prevent through safety measures and education.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Occupational Hazard">
  <data key="d0">Occupational Hazard</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Occupational Hazard refers to risks or harmful conditions in the work environment that employers must reduce through safety and health measures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 52">
  <data key="d0">Article 52</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 52 is a provision in Chinese labor law mandating employers to establish labor safety and health systems, enforce national regulations and standards, provide safety education, prevent workplace accidents, and reduce occupational hazards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a07aa9ee7ca74e51c0e67e4531d28af0</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Legal Binding Force">
  <data key="d0">Legal Binding Force</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Legal binding force refers to the enforceability of a labor contract under law, requiring both parties to fulfill their prescribed obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;Legal binding force refers to the enforceability and validity of a labor contract under law; invalid contracts lack this force from the time of conclusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1affc2633f7ab17127fc986e6c20944&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 107">
  <data key="d0">Article 107</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 107 is a provision specifying the effective date of the law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7bbdc9c932c7302eba4fe28c810a8b7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320869</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Law">
  <data key="d0">The Law</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Law refers to the legal statute containing Article 107, which comes into effect on January 1, 1995.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7bbdc9c932c7302eba4fe28c810a8b7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320869</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="January 1 1995">
  <data key="d0">January 1 1995</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">January 1, 1995 is the effective date stipulated for the law's implementation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d7bbdc9c932c7302eba4fe28c810a8b7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320869</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Medical Leave Period">
  <data key="d0">Medical Leave Period</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Medical Leave Period is a statutorily defined duration during which an Employee is excused from work due to illness or non-work-related injury, after which fitness for work is reassessed.&lt;SEP&gt;The medical leave period is a legally mandated timeframe during which a laborer recovering from illness or injury cannot be dismissed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Job Competency">
  <data key="d0">Job Competency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Job Competency refers to an Employee's ability to fulfill the essential duties of their position, and its deficiency may trigger employer-initiated training or reassignment before potential contract termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320879</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Original Employer">
  <data key="d0">Original Employer</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The original employer is the prior employer of a worker who has not yet terminated their labor contract, and may suffer economic losses due to the worker's new employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320889</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Economic Loss">
  <data key="d0">Economic Loss</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economic loss refers to financial harm incurred by the original employer as a result of the worker’s breach of contractual obligations.&lt;SEP&gt;Economic loss denotes financial damage incurred by the employer as a result of the laborer’s unlawful actions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Joint and Several Liability">
  <data key="d0">Joint and Several Liability</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Joint and several liability is a legal principle requiring the new employer to share responsibility for compensating the original employer’s economic losses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320889</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 99">
  <data key="d0">Article 99</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 99 is a provision in China’s Labor Law stipulating liability for employers hiring workers still under existing labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320889</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 43">
  <data key="d0">Article 43</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 43 is a specific provision in the Labor Law that prohibits employers from extending workers' working hours in violation of legal requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2dd1fd3462e1832af7cfde4c6f880f76</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320895</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Enterprises">
  <data key="d0">Enterprises</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Enterprises are entities encouraged by the State to establish industries or expand operations within the bounds of laws and administrative regulations to increase employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Institutions are organizations encouraged by the State to establish industries or expand operations within the bounds of laws and administrative regulations to increase employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Organizations">
  <data key="d0">Social Organizations</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Social Organizations are groups encouraged by the State to establish industries or expand operations within the bounds of laws and administrative regulations to increase employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Economic Development">
  <data key="d0">Economic Development</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Economic Development is a key strategy used by the State to foster job creation and expand employment opportunities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Development">
  <data key="d0">Social Development</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social Development is a key strategy used by the State to foster job creation and expand employment opportunities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Ten">
  <data key="d0">Article Ten</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Ten is a provision in Chinese law that outlines the State's responsibilities and measures for promoting employment through economic and social development and encouraging various organizations to expand operations legally.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e1896276de0d9340c0ef6a2e907293b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320914</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Dispute Mediation Committee">
  <data key="d0">Labor Dispute Mediation Committee</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Dispute Mediation Committee is established within employers and consists of employee representatives, employer representatives, and trade union representatives; it mediates labor disputes and its chairperson is appointed from the trade union representatives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320917</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Dispute Arbitration Committee">
  <data key="d0">Labor Dispute Arbitration Committee</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Dispute Arbitration Committee handles arbitration requests from parties involved in labor disputes, with members including representatives from labor administrative departments and other relevant entities.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Dispute Arbitration Committee is an authorized body empowered to confirm the invalidity of labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="People's Court">
  <data key="d0">People's Court</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The People's Court is the judicial body to which parties may appeal if dissatisfied with an arbitration award in a labor dispute.&lt;SEP&gt;The People's Court is a judicial institution with the authority to confirm the invalidity of labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Dispute">
  <data key="d0">Labor Dispute</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A Labor Dispute is a conflict between an employer and a worker that can be resolved through mediation, arbitration, litigation, or negotiation, guided by principles of legality, fairness, and timeliness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320917</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mediation">
  <data key="d0">Mediation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Mediation is a voluntary, non-binding process applicable to labor disputes, used both independently and within arbitration and litigation procedures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320918</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arbitration">
  <data key="d0">Arbitration</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Arbitration is a formal legal procedure for resolving labor disputes, initiated either after failed mediation or directly by a party, with decisions subject to judicial review.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320918</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Litigation">
  <data key="d0">Litigation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Litigation is a judicial process available to parties dissatisfied with an arbitration award in a labor dispute, conducted before the People's Court.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320918</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Individual Business Operations">
  <data key="d0">Individual Business Operations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Individual business operations refer to self-initiated commercial or service activities undertaken by workers to achieve employment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a84ae174a5d852490f9ffb8bbcec291</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320933</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Living Expenses">
  <data key="d0">Living Expenses</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Living Expenses refer to the minimum costs required for a worker and their average number of dependents to meet basic subsistence needs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add1965d088b328f8a7f228f9ba5c825</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320951</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Average Wage Level">
  <data key="d0">Average Wage Level</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Average Wage Level represents the mean earnings across all workers in society, used as a reference for setting fair wage floors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add1965d088b328f8a7f228f9ba5c825</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320951</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Productivity">
  <data key="d0">Labor Productivity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Productivity measures the output per unit of labor input and serves as an economic indicator influencing minimum wage adjustments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add1965d088b328f8a7f228f9ba5c825</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320951</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Status">
  <data key="d0">Employment Status</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment Status reflects the overall condition of the labor market, including job availability and unemployment rates, affecting wage policy decisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-add1965d088b328f8a7f228f9ba5c825</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320951</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regional Economic Development Disparities">
  <data key="d0">Regional Economic Development Disparities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
