  <data key="d0">Workers' Lawful Rights and Interests</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Workers' lawful rights and interests refer to the legally protected entitlements and protections of employees under labor law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-304f106d130307ad6bf0bdf62f720f8c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320972</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Penalty Provision">
  <data key="d0">Penalty Provision</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The penalty provision specifies that where other laws or administrative regulations already prescribe punishments for violations, those provisions shall apply.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-304f106d130307ad6bf0bdf62f720f8c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320972</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Other Laws and Administrative Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Other Laws and Administrative Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Other laws and administrative regulations are legal instruments outside the current law that may contain specific penalty clauses for labor rights violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-304f106d130307ad6bf0bdf62f720f8c</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320972</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Relevant Departments">
  <data key="d0">Relevant Departments</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Relevant Departments refer to governmental bodies associated with labor administration and regulation, working alongside or under the Labor Administration Department.&lt;SEP&gt;Relevant Departments are governmental bodies authorized to conduct labor inspections and enforce compliance alongside the Labor Administration Department.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321276</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Staff Members">
  <data key="d0">Staff Members</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Staff Members are personnel employed by the Labor Administration Department or relevant departments who carry out administrative duties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320998</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Administrative Sanction">
  <data key="d0">Administrative Sanction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Administrative Sanction is a disciplinary measure applied to staff members whose misconduct does not rise to the level of criminal offense.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320998</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Abuse of Power">
  <data key="d0">Abuse of Power</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Abuse of Power is a form of misconduct where staff members exceed or misuse their authority in violation of regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320998</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dereliction of Duty">
  <data key="d0">Dereliction of Duty</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dereliction of Duty is a form of misconduct involving negligence or failure to perform official responsibilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-534cee49a6033035c2c5393b14d42b64</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773320998</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
