<node id="People's Government at or Above the County Level">
  <data key="d0">People's Government at or Above the County Level</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The People's Government at or Above the County Level is a governmental body responsible for labor administration and supervision of employers' compliance with labor laws and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The People's Government at or Above the County Level is the local administrative authority empowered to supervise labor affairs and direct labor administrative departments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6446a7689e729164af31e8ab0faafc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ee12e2672dfb9fc10f84edd44b67880</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321145</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Law and Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Labor Law and Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Law and Regulations refer to the statutory framework governing employment relationships, worker rights, and employer obligations in China.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6446a7689e729164af31e8ab0faafc8b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321018</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 85">
  <data key="d0">Article 85</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 85 is a provision in China's Labor Law specifying the supervisory responsibilities of labor administrative departments over employers' compliance with labor laws and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6446a7689e729164af31e8ab0faafc8b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321018</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Employment">
  <data key="d0">Labor Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor employment refers to the provision and facilitation of job opportunities for citizens, promoted by the State through various measures.&lt;SEP&gt;Labor employment refers to the act of workers engaging in paid work, which is protected from discrimination under Article 12.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vocational Education">
  <data key="d0">Vocational Education</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Vocational education is a system of skill-based training and education developed by the State to enhance workforce capabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Standards">
  <data key="d0">Labor Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor standards are regulations established by the State to govern working conditions, rights, and responsibilities in employment relationships.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Social Income Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Social Income Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Social income regulation refers to the State's efforts to adjust and balance income distribution across society.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Relations Coordination">
  <data key="d0">Labor Relations Coordination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor relations coordination involves the State’s role in mediating and harmonizing interactions between employers and employees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Living Standards of Workers">
  <data key="d0">Living Standards of Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Living standards of workers refer to the overall quality of life of employed individuals, which the State aims to gradually improve.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321033</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Five">
  <data key="d0">Article Five</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Five is a provision in Chinese law that outlines the State's responsibilities regarding labor employment, vocational education, labor standards, income regulation, social insurance, labor relations coordination, and improvement of workers' living standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37520b7460881d90be5e94afa5fee4c5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321034</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 12">
  <data key="d0">Article 12</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 12 is a legal provision prohibiting employment discrimination based on ethnicity, race, gender, or religious belief.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ethnicity">
  <data key="d0">Ethnicity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ethnicity is a protected characteristic under Article 12, meaning employment decisions must not be influenced by it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Race">
  <data key="d0">Race</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Race is a protected characteristic under Article 12, meaning employment decisions must not be influenced by it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gender">
  <data key="d0">Gender</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gender is a protected characteristic under Article 12, meaning employment decisions must not be influenced by it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Religious Belief">
  <data key="d0">Religious Belief</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Religious belief is a protected characteristic under Article 12, meaning employment decisions must not be influenced by it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Discrimination">
  <data key="d0">Employment Discrimination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment discrimination refers to unfair treatment in hiring, promotion, or other employment practices based on prohibited grounds such as ethnicity, race, gender, or religious belief.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2f9cf51a71d05c5aaeae0c910ea62a37</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Workplace Accident Reporting and Handling System">
  <data key="d0">Workplace Accident Reporting and Handling System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A statutory system established by the State for the statistical reporting and processing of casualties occurring during labor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321061</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Occupational Disease Reporting and Handling System">
  <data key="d0">Occupational Disease Reporting and Handling System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A statutory system established by the State for the statistical reporting and processing of occupational diseases affecting workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321061</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 57">
  <data key="d0">Article 57</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 57 is a provision in Chinese labor legislation that mandates the establishment of statistical reporting and handling systems for workplace accidents and occupational diseases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b31fb50320a0aa42681462a5892c534</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321061</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Socialist Market Economy">
  <data key="d0">Socialist Market Economy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Socialist Market Economy is the economic system in the People's Republic of China that the Labor Law aims to support through appropriate labor institutional arrangements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Constitution of the People's Republic of China">
  <data key="d0">Constitution of the People's Republic of China</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Constitution of the People's Republic of China serves as the foundational legal basis upon which the Labor Law is formulated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Rights">
  <data key="d0">Labor Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Rights encompass statutory entitlements of workers, including equal employment, fair remuneration, rest and vacation, occupational safety and health, vocational training, social insurance, and labor dispute resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Obligations">
  <data key="d0">Labor Obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor Obligations refer to duties workers must fulfill, such as completing assigned tasks, improving vocational skills, complying with occupational safety and health regulations, and observing labor discipline and professional ethics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employer Rules and Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Employer Rules and Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Employer Rules and Regulations are internal systems that employers must legally establish and improve to safeguard workers' rights and ensure fulfillment of labor obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321077</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 1">
  <data key="d0">Article 1</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 1 of the Labor Law of the People's Republic of China states the law's purpose: to protect workers' rights, adjust labor relations, establish and maintain a labor system adapted to the socialist market economy, and promote economic development and social progress, based on the Constitution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 2">
  <data key="d0">Article 2</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 2 of the Labor Law of the People's Republic of China defines its scope of application, covering enterprises and individual economic organizations (collectively termed employers) and their workers within the People's Republic of China, as well as state organs, public institutions, and social organizations that enter into labor contracts with workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 3">
  <data key="d0">Article 3</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 3 of the Labor Law of the People's Republic of China enumerates workers' rights-including equal employment, remuneration, rest and vacation, occupational safety and health protection, vocational training, social insurance and welfare, and labor dispute resolution-as well as their obligations, such as completing work tasks, improving skills, complying with safety regulations, and observing labor discipline and professional ethics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 4">
  <data key="d0">Article 4</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 4 of the Labor Law of the People's Republic of China mandates that employers must lawfully formulate and improve internal rules and regulations to guarantee workers' rights and ensure fulfillment of labor obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3ef7680c783357332f2ef093d817c7f2</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321078</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Breach of Confidentiality">
  <data key="d0">Breach of Confidentiality</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Breach of confidentiality refers to the violation of agreed-upon confidentiality terms in a labor contract, potentially causing economic loss to the employer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Unauthorized Termination of Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Unauthorized Termination of Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Unauthorized termination refers to a laborer ending a labor contract in violation of legally prescribed conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 102">
  <data key="d0">Article 102</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 102 is a specific provision in the Labor Contract Law that stipulates compensation liability for laborers who unlawfully terminate contracts or breach confidentiality obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Contract System">
  <data key="d0">Labor Contract System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Contract System is a legal framework governing employment relationships, established by national law and implemented locally with specified procedural steps.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 106">
  <data key="d0">Article 106</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 106 is a provision specifying the authority of provincial-level governments to define implementation steps for the labor contract system and requiring reporting to the State Council.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="People's Republic of China">
  <data key="d0">People's Republic of China</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The People's Republic of China is the sovereign state whose national law governs the Labor Contract System and authorizes provincial governments to implement it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Provincial, Autonomous Region, and Municipality Directly Under the Central Government">
  <data key="d0">Provincial, Autonomous Region, and Municipality Directly Under the Central Government</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">These are first-level administrative divisions of the People's Republic of China where the Labor Contract System implementation steps are locally prescribed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-391c9ac1a44dcff50d59e13e3dd208b6</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Commercial Secret">
  <data key="d0">Commercial Secret</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A Commercial Secret refers to confidential business information protected under labor contract provisions to maintain competitive advantage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1a4ebf44debb9e60481cc178f07fa11</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321105</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 22">
  <data key="d0">Article 22</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 22 is a provision in Chinese labor law that permits inclusion of confidentiality clauses in labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1a4ebf44debb9e60481cc178f07fa11</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321105</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Contract Law of the People's Republic of China">
  <data key="d0">Labor Contract Law of the People's Republic of China</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Labor Contract Law of the People's Republic of China is the statutory legal framework governing labor contracts, under which Article 22 is enacted.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Contract Law of the People's Republic of China is the comprehensive statutory framework governing employment relationships, including protections against unjust termination as specified in Article 29.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1a4ebf44debb9e60481cc178f07fa11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321256</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Women">
  <data key="d0">Women</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Women are a demographic group granted equal employment rights with men under the specified regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0025690c407466c1d21fda9ca2cd0b52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Men">
  <data key="d0">Men</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Men are a demographic group with whom women share equal employment rights under the specified regulation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0025690c407466c1d21fda9ca2cd0b52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Rights">
  <data key="d0">Employment Rights</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment rights refer to the legal entitlements related to hiring, job assignment, and workplace treatment, guaranteed equally to women and men.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0025690c407466c1d21fda9ca2cd0b52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State-Designated Occupations">
  <data key="d0">State-Designated Occupations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">State-designated occupations are specific jobs or positions officially determined by the state as unsuitable for women, forming an exception to gender-based employment equality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0025690c407466c1d21fda9ca2cd0b52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Thirteen">
  <data key="d0">Article Thirteen</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Thirteen is a legal provision guaranteeing women equal employment rights with men, except for state-designated occupations unsuitable for women.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0025690c407466c1d21fda9ca2cd0b52</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="County-Level or Higher People's Government">
  <data key="d0">County-Level or Higher People's Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The County-Level or Higher People's Government has the authority to order production suspension and rectification in cases of serious labor safety violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Safety Facilities">
  <data key="d0">Labor Safety Facilities</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor safety facilities are physical installations required by national standards to ensure workplace safety.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Labor Hygiene Conditions">
  <data key="d0">Labor Hygiene Conditions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Labor hygiene conditions refer to environmental and health-related standards in the workplace mandated by national regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Major Accident">
  <data key="d0">Major Accident</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A major accident is a workplace incident resulting from unaddressed hazards, causing significant loss of life or property.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 92">
  <data key="d0">Article 92</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 92 is a provision in China's labor law specifying legal consequences for employers failing to meet labor safety and hygiene requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321127</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 18">
  <data key="d0">Article 18</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 18 is a legal provision specifying conditions under which labor contracts are deemed invalid.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Invalid Labor Contract">
  <data key="d0">Invalid Labor Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An invalid labor contract is one that violates laws or administrative regulations, or is concluded through fraud, coercion, or other improper means, and thus lacks legal binding force from inception.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law Violation">
  <data key="d0">Law Violation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Law violation refers to the breach of laws or administrative regulations in the formation of a labor contract, rendering it invalid under Article 18.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fraud or Coercion">
  <data key="d0">Fraud or Coercion</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fraud or coercion denotes improper means such as deception or threats used in concluding a labor contract, which invalidates it per Article 18.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b0d980fa13701d98c8fef09e4c134b5</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321144</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 86">
  <data key="d0">Article 86</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 86 is a provision in Chinese labor law that stipulates the supervisory and inspection duties of labor administrative departments at or above the county level.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8ee12e2672dfb9fc10f84edd44b67880</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321145</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 32">
  <data key="d0">Article 32</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 32 is a provision in China's Labor Law that enumerates specific circumstances under which a laborer may terminate a labor contract immediately by notifying the employer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Working Conditions">
  <data key="d0">Working Conditions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Working conditions refer to the environment, safety, tools, and other prerequisites provided by the employer as agreed upon in the labor contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321168</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Contract">
  <data key="d0">Employment Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The employment contract is a legally binding agreement between employer and employee, central to the provisions of this article.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321170</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 98">
  <data key="d0">Article 98</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 98 is a provision in China's Labor Law specifying employer liabilities for unlawful termination or delay in concluding employment contracts and the administrative remedies available.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321170</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Principle of Equality and Voluntariness">
  <data key="d0">Principle of Equality and Voluntariness</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">This principle requires that both parties to a labor contract enter into or modify the agreement freely and on equal footing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c60e5be371dfa1f9ec2c3f41c6c51bea</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Principle of Consensus Through Consultation">
  <data key="d0">Principle of Consensus Through Consultation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">This principle mandates that any establishment or amendment of a labor contract must result from mutual agreement reached through discussion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c60e5be371dfa1f9ec2c3f41c6c51bea</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Law and Administrative Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Law and Administrative Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">These are binding legal provisions established by state legislative and administrative authorities that labor contracts must not violate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c60e5be371dfa1f9ec2c3f41c6c51bea</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Seventeen">
  <data key="d0">Article Seventeen</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Seventeen is a provision in Chinese labor law that stipulates principles for establishing and amending labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c60e5be371dfa1f9ec2c3f41c6c51bea</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321201</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Minor Under Sixteen">
  <data key="d0">Minor Under Sixteen</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A minor under sixteen refers to a person younger than sixteen years old, whose employment is generally prohibited but allowed in certain sectors under national regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;A minor under sixteen refers to a person below the age of sixteen, whose employment is prohibited by labor law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cultural Institutions">
  <data key="d0">Cultural Institutions</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Cultural institutions are organizations involved in arts and entertainment and may employ minors under sixteen in accordance with national regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sports Organizations">
  <data key="d0">Sports Organizations</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Sports organizations are entities engaged in athletic training and competition and may employ minors under sixteen in compliance with national regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Special Craft Units">
  <data key="d0">Special Craft Units</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Special craft units are organizations practicing traditional or specialized crafts and may employ minors under sixteen subject to national regulatory requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Compulsory Education">
  <data key="d0">Compulsory Education</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Compulsory education is a legally mandated educational requirement that must be safeguarded for minors even when employed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Fifteen">
  <data key="d0">Article Fifteen</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Fifteen is a legal provision prohibiting employers from hiring minors under sixteen years of age, with exceptions for cultural, sports, and special craft units subject to national regulations and compulsory education safeguards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-982fdc171e24d19c2286c2a017fe7f13</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321209</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="People's Republic of China Labor Law">
  <data key="d0">People's Republic of China Labor Law</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The People's Republic of China Labor Law is a statutory legal document enacted by the National People's Congress of the People's Republic of China to regulate labor relations and protect the rights and interests of workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d3655737d1346d3b8f895dafbf249462</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321219</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employees">
  <data key="d0">Employees</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Employees are the workers who may be subject to reduction and must be informed and consulted during the process; they also hold priority re-employment rights within six months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Staff Reduction">
  <data key="d0">Staff Reduction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Staff reduction is a legally regulated personnel adjustment measure permitted only under conditions of statutory restructuring or serious operational hardship.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Priority Re-Employment">
  <data key="d0">Priority Re-Employment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Priority re-employment is the legal obligation of an employer to give preferential hiring consideration to previously laid-off employees within six months of their termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Statutory Restructuring">
  <data key="d0">Statutory Restructuring</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Statutory restructuring refers to the legally mandated reorganization process undertaken by employers facing imminent bankruptcy, serving as a condition for lawful staff reduction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Severe Operational Hardship">
  <data key="d0">Severe Operational Hardship</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Severe operational hardship denotes a critical deterioration in an employer's business conditions, constituting another legally recognized basis for staff reduction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321222</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article Seven">
  <data key="d0">Article Seven</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Article Seven is a legal provision granting laborers the right to join and organize trade unions and affirming the independent operation of trade unions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7772034814a251985224602f1dd80c02</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321227</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Regulation Department">
  <data key="d0">Market Regulation Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Market Regulation Department is the government body authorized to revoke business licenses in cases of serious labor law violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Business License">
  <data key="d0">Business License</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A business license is an official document permitting an organization to operate legally, which may be revoked for severe violations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 94">
  <data key="d0">Article 94</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 94 is a provision in Chinese labor legislation specifying penalties for illegal employment of minors under sixteen.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321244</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Work-Related Injury">
  <data key="d0">Work-Related Injury</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A work-related injury is a physical harm sustained during employment and confirmed to result in partial or total loss of working capacity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Maternity Leave">
  <data key="d0">Maternity Leave</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Maternity leave is a legally guaranteed period following childbirth during which female laborers are protected from contract termination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nursing Period">
  <data key="d0">Nursing Period</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The nursing period refers to the time after maternity leave when a female laborer is breastfeeding and remains protected from dismissal.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 29">
  <data key="d0">Article 29</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 29 is a provision in the Labor Contract Law specifying circumstances under which employers may not terminate labor contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321255</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter Seven">
  <data key="d0">Chapter Seven</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter Seven is a section of a legal or regulatory document focusing on special protections for female workers and underage workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cdfe4fd7432c0c1b10d2636d5f862da7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321260</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Underage Workers">
  <data key="d0">Underage Workers</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Underage workers refer to individuals below the legal working age who are granted special protections under labor regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cdfe4fd7432c0c1b10d2636d5f862da7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321260</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Special Protection">
  <data key="d0">Special Protection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Special protection denotes legally mandated safeguards for vulnerable worker groups such as female and underage workers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cdfe4fd7432c0c1b10d2636d5f862da7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321260</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter Seven Female Workers and Underage Workers Special Protection">
  <data key="d0">Chapter Seven Female Workers and Underage Workers Special Protection</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter Seven is titled 'Female Workers and Underage Workers Special Protection' and constitutes a formal section of labor legislation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cdfe4fd7432c0c1b10d2636d5f862da7</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321260</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chapter Two">
  <data key="d0">Chapter Two</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Chapter Two is titled "Promoting Employment" and focuses on employment-related policies or initiatives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1ee1394b419d5bc0695ef81391d0c4b8</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Employment Promotion">
  <data key="d0">Employment Promotion</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Employment Promotion refers to strategies, measures, or policies aimed at increasing job opportunities and reducing unemployment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1ee1394b419d5bc0695ef81391d0c4b8</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321267</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Whistleblower">
  <data key="d0">Whistleblower</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Whistleblower is an individual who reports violations of labor law and is protected from retaliation under this provision.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321276</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 101">
  <data key="d0">Article 101</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 101 is a legal provision stipulating penalties for employers who obstruct labor inspections or retaliate against whistleblowers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
  <data key="d4">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1773321276</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<edge source="Article 37" target="Article 36">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Article 37 explicitly references and depends on the working hour system defined in Article 36 to establish fair labor quotas and remuneration standards.</data>
  <data key="d9">legal reference,regulatory foundation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320346</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Article 37" target="Employer">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The employer must adhere to the requirements stipulated in Article 37 when managing piece-rate workers’ workload and compensation.</data>
  <data key="d9">legal compliance,regulatory obligation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320346</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Article 37" target="Labor Law of the People's Republic of China">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Article 37 is a specific provision embedded within the Labor Law of the People's Republic of China.</data>
  <data key="d9">legal hierarchy,statutory codification</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320346</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Piece-Rate Worker">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The employer is legally obligated to set appropriate labor quotas and piece-rate pay standards for the piece-rate worker in compliance with Articles 36 and 37.</data>
  <data key="d9">employment relationship,wage determination</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-db161f575c0e9349bf3b18d1733f159c</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320346</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Labor Contract">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The employer is a party to the labor contract and holds statutory authority to terminate it under specified conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer enters into and may lawfully terminate the labor contract under specified articles of the Labor Law.&lt;SEP&gt;The labor contract defines the rights and obligations of the employer within the labor relationship.&lt;SEP&gt;The Employer has the authority to terminate the Labor Contract, subject to legal and regulatory compliance.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer is a signatory to the labor contract and must perform the obligations defined within it.&lt;SEP&gt;The Employer holds the statutory right to terminate the Labor Contract under defined conditions, subject to procedural requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer is bound by the labor contract to pay remuneration and provide agreed working conditions; failure constitutes grounds for termination.</data>
  <data key="d9">compliance,contractual authority,contractual obligations,contractual party,contractual relationship,legal agreement,legal obligation,legal relationship,obligation,rights and obligations,termination authority,termination right</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25702dd54870df07d3bedb29b9496851&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7440e9a9d68a40eb06fc88eaf48bf3a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1e934469e0af82604f570bd7744c5cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1affc2633f7ab17127fc986e6c20944&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5cd7ed5505461fd7709fa8b54316269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a093f2a713e82a84a2df8dea3ab064</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773321169</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Article Twenty-Five">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The employer's right to terminate a labor contract under specified conditions is derived from Article Twenty-Five of the labor law.</data>
  <data key="d9">legal authority,statutory basis</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-0f133335b434209fb07a50ad3e0a2f33</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320371</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Overtime Work">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Employer is legally required to pay at least 150% of normal wages for Overtime Work.</data>
  <data key="d9">legal obligation,wage payment</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-eb26be1be6719b2d63eda122721b5d68</data>
