</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Worker">
  <data key="d7">6.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Employer is legally required to pay the Worker a wage no lower than the local Minimum Wage Standard.&lt;SEP&gt;The Employer issues directives-including potentially unlawful and hazardous work orders-to the Worker.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer must consult with the worker before extending working hours.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer hires the worker, triggering legal obligations under labor law.&lt;SEP&gt;The Employer and Worker are the two primary parties involved in labor disputes governed by statutory resolution procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer has a legal obligation to guarantee the worker's right to at least one day of rest per week.</data>
  <data key="d9">command relationship,consultation,dispute parties,employment obligation,employment relationship,hiring,labor protection,labor regulation,wage obligation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11661d5949c7a4c46892595299c2a3db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-484ec462bb336f0faad2e38a9ab16421&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15db89e812c6ec17f40e3e2ae7f1d0cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bca3d7a5b26e41a901895456edf1d72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1b224bc392defbea2ebc9ea123f70db</data>
  <data key="d11">/Users/pysama/first_prize_RAG/dataset/labor_law.md</data>
  <data key="d12">1773320969</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Employer" target="Minimum Wage Standard">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Employer must ensure that wages paid to Workers meet or exceed the applicable Minimum Wage Standard.</data>
  <data key="d9">compliance requirement,legal obligation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-9a17dbf9d68b3a46e25ed3308c88ffbf</data>
