<edge source="Employer" target="Laborer">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The laborer must deliver written notice to the employer as a prerequisite for terminating the labor contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Laborers engage in equal negotiation with employers to protect their lawful rights and interests.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer is legally obligated to pay wages to the laborer during statutory holidays, marriage leave, bereavement leave, and lawful social activities.&lt;SEP&gt;The laborer has a contractual relationship with the employer and bears compensation liability if their actions cause economic loss.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer is legally prohibited from terminating the laborer's contract under the circumstances specified in Article 29.</data>
  <data key="d9">contractual duty,contractual relationship,employment obligation,employment protection,employment relationship,equal negotiation,legal restriction,liability,rights protection,wage payment</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-82eedbfc6978ce7b8284768afbfab33f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6768f8c1f0e359974ecafdba6b02c7c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-29625ec97f3aa262c09d4aa1c862291b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01ab560573c5cd878f4442fcbbac6cef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e07869d7cd11d05487d341eeabe67b63</data>
