<edge source="Employer" target="Labor Administration Department">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Labor Administration Department has the authority to order employers to pay overdue social insurance premiums.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department orders the employer to correct violations of labor law.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administration Department enforces compliance by ordering corrective action and imposing fines on employers violating Article 94.&lt;SEP&gt;The Employer may unreasonably obstruct the Labor Administration Department’s exercise of inspection authority.</data>
  <data key="d9">administrative order,administrative penalty,obstruction,regulatory enforcement,regulatory violation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-1c3f29bba2e48ace661e0e106cd6c106&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f221ff98ea22e9acb2603a0162c0526&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49dfcfe749ae5b7a3d964afb5d16559b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55fedf8879833ede48386f292722cc7d</data>
