  <data key="d7">2.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Employer bears Compensation Liability as a direct consequence of causing damage through an invalid employment contract.&lt;SEP&gt;An employer must bear compensation liability when its violation of protective provisions causes actual harm to a female worker or underage worker.</data>
  <data key="d9">damage redress,legal consequence,legal obligation</data>
