<edge source="Employer" target="Labor Administrative Department">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Labor Administrative Department has the authority to order corrections and impose fines on employers who violate protections for female and underage workers.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administrative Department supervises employers and enforces corrective measures-including warnings, orders to rectify, fines, and compensation mandates-for labor law violations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administrative Department conducts inspections of employers and has the authority to stop and order correction of violations of labor laws and regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Labor Administrative Department has the authority to order corrections and impose fines on employers violating labor safety regulations.&lt;SEP&gt;The employer must report the planned staff reduction to the labor administrative department as a mandatory procedural step.</data>
  <data key="d9">administrative oversight,administrative penalty,compliance enforcement,enforcement action,legal supervision,regulatory enforcement,regulatory oversight,reporting</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-add3425ac8339584dcc65694586b9a03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a7d21f4dbacb9974d96f6a4b7cd73aa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6446a7689e729164af31e8ab0faafc8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d8030db75e52bd9e7110fb8f615de79&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09d777684aee4aa08ce23008df6295e7</data>
